<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2020</DATELINE><TITLE>Proposed prevention and control of 2019 novel coronavirus infection in neonates</TITLE><BODY>Following an outbreak of pneumonia caused by 2019 novel coronavirus (2019-nCoV) which has spread in China, the National Health Commission of China issued public health policies and implemented interventions for control and prevention of the epidemic. Given that the maternal-fetus vertical transmission caused by 2019-nCoV is still unidentified, as a special population, neonates need a targeted clinical management. This detailed plan of care is proposed to provide better prevention and control of neonatal 2019-nCoV infection.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>